default as its value plummeted from £13bn to £3bn resulting in huge shareholder loss
default– in essence, those behind the group failed to meet the standards of a public company.
defaultThe second reputational hit on the LSE involved Bumi PLC
default,
default described as ‘the biggest corpora
defaultte scandal to hit London for two decades’ by the Wall Street Journal.
default 
defaultIt has been 
defaultrevealed that Bumi was sitting on unaccounted payments of $201m – investors’ expectations about corporate governance at Bumi, assumed from being listed on the LSE, were not 
defaultmet. Bumi
default’s shares 
defaulthave
default fallen 
defaultby a quarter in value.
defaultThese cases have dealt a huge blow to the reputation of London as a centre for excellence in business. However, in spite of these warning signs, London continues to encourage extractives companies to it
defaults exchange. Glencore/X
